name: LLA, Pediatric Lower Extremity Function(Mobility)
description: Mark one box per row; for each question you can choose the following answers from 4 - 0
child.1: LLA, I could get down on my knees without holding on to something
child.2: LLA, I could keep up when I played with other kids
child.3: LLA, I could walk for 15 minutes
child.4: LLA, I could walk between rooms
child.5: LLA, I could get on and off the toilet without using my arms
child.6: LLA, I could get on and off a low chair
child.7: LLA, I could get up from the floor by myself
child.8: LLA, I could sit on a bench without support for 15 minutes?
child.9: LLA, I could stand on my tiptoes to reach for something
child.10: LLA, I could stand on my tiptoes to put something (e.g. a pack of sugar) on a shelf
child.11: LLA, I could walk on slightly uneven surfaces (such as cracked pavement)
child.12: LLA, I could walk on rough, uneven surfaces (such as lawns/ fields)
child.13: LLA, I could walk up and down ramps and hills
child.14: LLA, I could walk up and down curbs (steps)
child.15: LLA, I could get in and out of a bus
child.16: LLA, I could get in and out of a car
child.17: LLA, I could walk across the room
child.18: LLA, I could walk while wearing a backpack full of books
child.19: LLA, I could bend over to pick something up
child.20: LLA, I could exercise that others my age can do

name: LLA, Lower Extremity Functional Index (LEFI)
description: Mark one box per row; for each question you can choose the following answers from 0 - 4
child.1: LLA, Any of your usual work, housework or school activities
child.2: LLA, Your usual hobbies, recreational or sporting activities
child.3: LLA, Getting into or out of the bath (into the bathtub)
child.5: LLA, Putting on your shoes and socks
child.7: LLA, Lifting an object (like a bag of groceries) from the floor
child.8: LLA, Performing light activities around your home (changing bulbs, decorating, cleaning)
child.9: LLA, Performing heavy activities around your home (gardening, maintenance etc.)
child.10: LLA, Getting into or out of a car
child.13: LLA, Going up or down 10 stairs (about one flight of stairs)
child.14: LLA, Standing for one hour (e.g. waiting in a line)
child.15: LLA, Sitting for one hour (e.g. wedding)
child.18: LLA, Making sharp turns while running fast
